    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the sentence: </span><span class=\"english\">“Education also fosters critical thinking.”</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>5</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">The given line has been collected from the lesson ‘Why Education’ of the text book. Education plays a crucial role in developing critical thinking by interacting individuals to diverse perspectives and complex situations, challenging them to </span><span class=\"english\">analyse</span><span class=\"english\"> and evaluate problems systematically. It encourages problem-solving and analytical skills, helping students to approach issues methodically and draw informed conclusions. By fostering </span><span class=\"english\">curiosity and </span><span class=\"english\">scepticism</span><span class=\"english\">, education promotes questioning and inquiry, essential for critical thinking. It also enhances communication skills, enabling clear articulation and effective argumentation, and encourages reflective thinking, allowing individuals to align their beliefs with new knowledge. Thus, education equips people with the tools needed to navigate and make informed decisions in a complex world.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Identification of the Quote and Source </span><span class=\"english\">---------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The given line has been collected from the lesson ‘Why Education’ of the text book.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">\"Why Education: A Role in Critical Thinking\") </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">) ------------------</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">• Education fosters critical thinking by exposing individuals to diverse perspectives and complex situations.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• It encourages systematic problem-solving and analytical skills.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Fosters curiosity and skepticism, promoting questioning and inquiry.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Enhances communication skills, enabling clear argumentation.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Encourages reflective thinking, aligning beliefs with new knowledge.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Equips individuals with tools for informed decision-making in a complex world.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Instructions</span><span class=\"english\">:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">**For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span><span> </span></p>"
